## Backend Architecture

### Layer Structure
```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  Controller Layer              │  ← HTTP endpoints, request/response
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│  Service Layer                 │  ← Business logic, validation
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│  Repository Layer              │  ← Database queries (Spring Data JPA)
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│  Model/Entity Layer            │  ← Database entities
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│  DTO Layer                     │  ← Data transfer objects
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Naming Conventions

#### DTOs
- **Always include "DTO" suffix** for clarity (preferred standard)
  - Example: `MovieDTO`, `PromotionDTO`, `UserProfileDTO`
- **RequestDTO**: Incoming data (POST/PUT body)
  - Example: `PaymentCardRequestDTO`, `RegisterRequestDTO`
  - Note: Some legacy files use just `Request` (e.g., `LoginRequest`) - will be standardized to `LoginRequestDTO` in future
- **ResponseDTO**: Outgoing data (API response)
  - Example: `PaymentCardResponseDTO`, `UserProfileResponseDTO`
  - Note: Some legacy files use just `Response` (e.g., `AuthResponse`) - will be standardized to `AuthResponseDTO` in future
- **DTO**: Used for both request and response (bidirectional)
  - Example: `MovieDTO`, `PromotionDTO`

#### Controllers
- **Suffix with `Controller`**: `MovieController`, `UserController`
- **RESTful naming**: Use standard HTTP methods
  ```java
  @GetMapping("/movies")           // Get all
  @GetMapping("/movies/{id}")      // Get one
  @PostMapping("/movies")          // Create
  @PutMapping("/movies/{id}")      // Update
  @DeleteMapping("/movies/{id}")   // Delete
  ```

#### Services
- **Suffix with `Service`**: `MovieService`, `PaymentCardService`
- **Business logic methods**: `createMovie`, `validateCard`, `processBooking`
- **DTO to Entity conversion**: Handle in service, NOT controller
- **Naming convention**: `createMovie(MovieDTO)` NOT `createMovieFromDTO(MovieDTO)`
  - Method name matches entity, parameter type shows it takes DTO
  - Consistent with other services (e.g., PromotionService.createPromotion(PromotionDTO))

#### Repositories
- **Suffix with `Repository`**: `MovieRepository`, `UserRepository`
- **Extend JPA interfaces**: `JpaRepository<Movie, Long>`

### Environment Variables

**Backend requires environment variables:**
- **Required**: `DATABASE_URL`, `DATABASE_USERNAME`, `DATABASE_PASSWORD`
- **Setup**: Source `set_env.sh` before running backend
  - Mac/Linux: `source set_env.sh && mvn spring-boot:run`
  - Windows: `set_env.ps1`
- **Error Handling**: Application fails with clear error if env vars not set
- **Configuration**: Database config in `application.properties` uses env vars for security

### Backend Layer Separation

**Controller Layer (THIN - Target: < 5 lines per method)**
```java
@PostMapping("/create")
public ResponseEntity<?> createMovie(@RequestBody MovieDTO dto) {
    try {
        Movie created = movieService.createMovie(dto);  // Delegate to service
        return ResponseEntity.ok(created);
    } catch (Exception e) {
        return ResponseEntity.badRequest().body("Error: " + e.getMessage());
    }
}
```

**Service Layer (THICK - Contains all business logic)**
```java
@CacheEvict(value = {"nowPlayingMovies", "upcomingMovies"}, allEntries = true)
public Movie createMovie(MovieDTO movieDTO) {
    // DTO to Entity conversion in service
    Movie newMovie = new Movie();
    newMovie.setTitle(movieDTO.getTitle());
    newMovie.setStatus(MovieStatus.upcoming);
    // ... all conversion logic here
    
    return movieRepository.save(newMovie);
}
```

**What Belongs Where**:
- **Controller**: HTTP concerns (request/response, status codes, headers)
- **Service**: Business logic (validation, transformation, DTO conversion, transactions)
- **Repository**: Data access (queries, persistence)

### Code Organization
```
src/main/java/com/acm/cinema_ebkg_system/
├── config/                # Configuration classes
│   ├── CacheConfig.java
│   ├── SecurityConfig.java
│   └── WebConfig.java
├── controller/            # REST controllers
├── service/               # Business logic
├── repository/            # Data access
├── model/                 # JPA entities
├── dto/                   # Data transfer objects
│   ├── auth/
│   ├── movie/
│   ├── payment/
│   └── user/
├── filter/                # Request filters (JWT)
├── util/                  # Utility classes
└── enums/                 # Enumerations
```

