## Component Reusability Rules

### Component Size & Complexity Limits

**Hard Limits:**
- **Component size**: Max 200-300 lines, split if larger
- **State management**: Max 5-7 `useState` hooks per component
- **If exceeded**: Extract logic to custom hooks or split into smaller components

**When to Extract:**
- Component >300 lines → Split into smaller components
- Component has >7 `useState` hooks → Create custom hook
- API calls in component → Move to custom hook
- Business logic in component → Extract to hook or utility
- Formatting functions in component → Move to `utils/`

### Pages Should Be Lightweight (Target: < 100 lines)
```tsx
// GOOD: Page just calls hook and renders
export default function PaymentsPage() {
  const { userId } = useUserId();
  const payment = usePaymentCards(userId);  // ONE hook call
  
  return (
    <div>
      <NavBar />
      <UserNavTabs activeTab="payments" />
      <PaymentCardsList 
        cards={payment.paymentCards}
        onEdit={payment.openEdit}
        onDelete={payment.handleDelete}
      />
      <PaymentCardModal
        isOpen={payment.isOpen}
        onSubmit={payment.handleSubmit}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

// BAD: Page contains business logic
export default function PaymentsPage() {
  const [cards, setCards] = useState([]);
  const [mode, setMode] = useState('Add');
  
  const handleSubmit = async (formData) => {
    if (mode === 'Add') { /* logic */ }
    else { /* logic */ }
  };
  
  // ... 200 lines of logic
}
```

### Component Composition Over Monoliths
```tsx
// GOOD: Composed components
<SelectedMovie>
  <SelectedMovieInfo />
  <SelectedMovieCredits />
  <SelectedMovieShowtimes />
</SelectedMovie>

// BAD: Monolithic component
<SelectedMovie />  // 500 lines of JSX inside
```

### Props > Context (for most cases)
- Use props for component-to-child communication
- Use context only for truly global state (auth, theme)
- Don't overuse context (causes unnecessary re-renders)

---

## Error Handling Rules

### Frontend Error Handling
```typescript
// ALWAYS provide user-friendly messages
try {
  await movieClient.getMovieById(id);
} catch (error) {
  setError('Failed to load movie details. Please try again.');
  // NOT: setError(error.message) - too technical
}

// ALWAYS have loading states
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);

// ALWAYS reset error state before retrying
const retry = () => {
  setError(null);
  fetchData();
};
```

### Backend Error Handling
```java
// ALWAYS return appropriate HTTP status codes
@ExceptionHandler(ResourceNotFoundException.class)
public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponse> handleNotFound(ResourceNotFoundException ex) {
    return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)
        .body(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessage()));
}

// ALWAYS log errors (but don't expose internals to client)
catch (Exception e) {
    log.error("Database error processing payment", e);
    throw new ServiceException("Payment processing failed"); // Generic message to client
}
```

---

## Testing Rules

### What to Test
1. **Business logic** (service layer methods)
2. **API endpoints** (controller integration tests)
3. **Utility functions** (pure function unit tests)
4. **Complex components** (React component tests)

### What NOT to Test
1. **Simple getters/setters**
2. **Framework code** (Spring Security, Next.js routing)
3. **Third-party libraries**
4. **Generated code** (Lombok, DTO builders)

---

## Performance Rules

### Caching Strategy
1. **Use Spring Cache** for expensive queries (movie lists, genres)
2. **Set appropriate TTL** (5-10 min for volatile data, 1 hour for static)
3. **Evict on mutations** (@CacheEvict on create/update/delete)
4. **Consider cache size** (limit to 100-1000 entries)

### React Performance
1. **Use useMemo** for expensive calculations
2. **Use useCallback** for functions passed as props
3. **Use React.memo** for pure components
4. **Lazy load** heavy components (React.lazy, Next.js dynamic)

### Database Performance
1. **Use pagination** for large result sets
2. **Use indexes** on frequently queried columns
3. **Avoid N+1 queries** (use JPA fetch joins)
4. **Use DTOs** to limit data transfer (MovieSummary vs Movie)

---

## Security Rules

### Frontend Security
1. **NEVER store sensitive data** in localStorage/cookies without encryption
2. **ALWAYS validate user input** before sending to backend
3. **Use HTTPS** in production
4. **Sanitize user-generated content** (XSS prevention)

### Backend Security
1. **ALWAYS validate input** (@Valid, @NotNull, @Size)
2. **Use parameterized queries** (prevents SQL injection)
3. **Hash passwords** (BCrypt, never plain text)
4. **Rate limit** sensitive endpoints (login, register)
5. **Use ROLE-based access** (ROLE_USER, ROLE_ADMIN)

---

## File Management & Legacy Code

### Documentation Files
- **No MD File Explosion**: Do not create multiple markdown files unnecessarily
- **Update Existing Docs**: Modify existing documentation instead of creating new files
- **Temporary Files**: Clean up analysis/temporary files after use
- **Consolidate**: Keep related information in single files

### Legacy Code & File Deletion

**Check Usage Before Deletion:**
1. Search codebase for imports/references using `grep` or codebase search
2. Check if used in frontend (API calls, imports)
3. Check if used in backend (controllers, services, repositories)
4. Document if legacy/unused before removal

**Legacy Code Identification:**
- Unused controllers/services (no frontend calls)
- Deprecated DTOs (replaced by newer versions)
- Duplicate functionality (old vs new implementation)
- Dead code paths (commented out, TODO markers)

**Refactoring Safety:**
- Ensure replacement exists and works
- Update all references before deletion
- Consider deprecation warnings before removal
- Test after removing legacy code

---

## Git Commit Rules

### Commit Message Format
```
<type>: <short description>

<optional longer description>

<optional footer>
```

### Types
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code refactoring (no behavior change)
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Formatting changes (no code change)
- `test`: Adding/updating tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

### Examples
```
feat: implement virtual proxy for movie details

- Created movieClient.ts facade
- Added getMovieById to fetch full movie entity
- Updated SelectedMovie to fetch cast/directors on click

Closes #42
```

---

## Dependency & Breakage Analysis (CRITICAL)

**Before modifying any code, you MUST:**

### 1. Trace All Usages
- Use `grep` to find all imports/usages of the function/component/hook
- Use codebase search to find indirect dependencies
- Check both frontend and backend if applicable
- Verify no other files import or depend on what you're changing

### 2. Analyze Type Signature Changes
- **Breaking changes**: Changing `function(x: number)` → `function(x: number | null)`
  - GOOD: Backward compatible - `number` can be passed to `number | null`
  - WARNING: Check all call sites handle `null` properly
- **Removing functions**: If removing function, verify no imports exist
- **Changing return types**: `number` → `number | null` requires all callers to handle `null`

### 3. Consider Edge Cases
- **SSR (Server-Side Rendering)**: 
  - `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` unavailable → functions return `null`
  - Client-side hydration may have different values → potential hydration mismatch
  - Verify components handle `null` gracefully during SSR
- **Null/undefined handling**:
  - API calls with `null` userId → URL becomes `/api/user/profile?userId=null` (verify backend handles this)
  - `useEffect` dependencies with `null` → may cause unnecessary re-renders
  - Conditional rendering with `null` → ensure UI doesn't break
- **Error states**:
  - Failed API calls → verify error handling doesn't crash
  - Missing tokens → verify graceful degradation
  - Network failures → verify user feedback

### 4. Verify Hook Dependencies
- **useEffect dependencies**: Changing type may affect dependency arrays
- **Hook return values**: Changing hook return types affects all consumers
- **Context providers**: Changing context values affects all consumers

### 5. Test Scenarios (Mental Checklist)
- [ ] **Happy path**: Normal usage works
- [ ] **Null/undefined**: Functions handle missing values
- [ ] **SSR**: Server-side rendering doesn't crash
- [ ] **Hydration**: Client-side hydration matches server
- [ ] **Error states**: Failures are handled gracefully
- [ ] **Type safety**: TypeScript catches type mismatches

### 6. Document Edge Cases
- Add brief comments for non-obvious edge cases
- Document SSR considerations
- Note any breaking changes in function signatures

---

## Refactoring Checklist

Before refactoring:
- [ ] Read existing code thoroughly
- [ ] Identify all usages (search codebase)
- [ ] Document current behavior
- [ ] Write tests (if not already covered)

During refactoring:
- [ ] Make small, incremental changes
- [ ] Test after each change
- [ ] Keep existing tests passing
- [ ] Don't change behavior (unless that's the goal)

After refactoring:
- [ ] Run full test suite
- [ ] Check for linter errors
- [ ] Update documentation
- [ ] Review git diff

---

## Questions to Ask Before Coding

1. **Does this follow SOLID principles?**
2. **Is this DRY (not duplicating existing code)?**
3. **Does this fit our architecture?**
4. **Will this break existing functionality?** (Trace dependencies first!)
5. **Is this the Single Source of Truth?**
6. **Can this be reused elsewhere?**
7. **Is error handling consistent?**
8. **Are naming conventions followed?**
9. **Is this testable?**
10. **Would I understand this code in 6 months?**
11. **Does this duplicate existing utilities?** (Check `utils/`, especially `auth.ts`)
12. **Are comments brief and explain WHY not WHAT?**
13. **Is component size <300 lines and state management <7 hooks?**
14. **Have I considered SSR/hydration edge cases?**
15. **Am I using `null` correctly (not `0` as sentinel)?**

---

## Red Flags (Don't Do This)

- Creating duplicate code when SSoT exists
- Putting business logic in controllers
- Putting API calls in components (use hooks/clients)
- Using `any` without type annotations
- Ignoring TypeScript errors
- Copying code without understanding it
- Creating files with vague names (`util.ts`, `helper.tsx`)
- Hard-coding values that should be configurable
- Skipping error handling
- Writing 500-line functions
- Using magic numbers without constants
- Mixing concerns (display + logic in one component)
- **Using emojis in code or comments**
- **Using arrow symbols (→) in comments**
- **Verbose comments explaining obvious code**
- Duplicating auth/token logic instead of using `utils/auth.ts`
- Manual JWT decoding instead of using `getUserIdFromToken()`
- Using `0` or `-1` as sentinel values instead of `null`
- Using `||` for fallbacks when `??` is correct (breaks with falsy values like `0`)
- Components >300 lines without splitting
- Components >7 `useState` hooks without extracting to custom hook
- Creating new markdown files instead of updating existing docs

---

## Decision Making Process

1. **Analyze**: Review existing code patterns and structures
2. **Trace Dependencies**: Find all usages and potential breakage points (see Dependency & Breakage Analysis)
3. **Argue**: Consider multiple approaches and their trade-offs
4. **Decide**: Choose solution that best fits SOLID principles and existing architecture
5. **Verify**: Check edge cases, SSR, null handling, error states
6. **Document**: Add brief comments explaining design decisions and edge cases

---

## UI/UX Design Conventions

### Color System (TailwindCSS)

**Primary Brand Colors:**
- `acm-pink`: Primary CTA color (`#FF478B`, `#FF3290` on hover)
- `acm-orange`: Secondary CTA color, used in gradients
- Gradients: `bg-gradient-to-r from-acm-pink to-acm-orange`

**Backgrounds:**
- Main background: `bg-black` or `bg-[#1C1C1C]`
- Cards/Panels: `bg-white/10` or `bg-black/50` with `backdrop-blur-md`
- Overlays: `bg-black/50` or `bg-black/70` with `backdrop-blur-sm`
- Hover states: `hover:bg-black/70`, `hover:bg-white/20`

**Text Colors:**
- Primary text: `text-white`
- Secondary text: `text-white/80`, `text-white/60`
- Tertiary text: `text-white/40`, `text-gray-400`, `text-gray-500`
- Error text: `text-red-400`, `text-red-200`
- Success text: `text-green-400`

**Borders:**
- Subtle borders: `border border-white/10`, `border-white/20`
- Hover borders: `hover:border-acm-pink/50`, `hover:border-white/40`
- Active/Selected: `border-acm-pink`, `border-2 border-acm-pink`

### Interactive Elements

**CRITICAL: ALL interactive elements MUST have `cursor-pointer`**

**Button Standards:**

1. **Primary CTA Buttons:**
```tsx
className="px-6 py-3 rounded-md font-afacad font-bold text-white bg-gradient-to-r from-acm-pink to-acm-orange hover:brightness-110 transition-all cursor-pointer disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
```

2. **Secondary Buttons:**
```tsx
className="px-4 py-2 rounded-md font-afacad font-bold text-white border-2 border-white/20 hover:border-white/40 transition-colors cursor-pointer"
```

3. **Icon Buttons:**
```tsx
className="bg-black/50 hover:bg-black/70 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-full p-2 text-white hover:text-acm-pink transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer border border-white/20 hover:border-acm-pink/50"
```

4. **Destructive Actions:**
```tsx
className="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300 transition-colors cursor-pointer"
```

**Link Standards:**
```tsx
// Navigation links
className="text-white hover:text-acm-pink transition-colors cursor-pointer"

// Active navigation (with underline indicator)
className="relative font-bold text-acm-pink cursor-pointer"
// Add: <span className="absolute -bottom-2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-8 h-0.5 bg-acm-pink rounded-full" />
```

**Input Standards:**
```tsx
className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-md bg-white/10 border border-white/20 text-white placeholder-white/60 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-acm-pink focus:border-transparent"
```

**Select Dropdowns:**
```tsx
className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-md bg-white/10 border border-white/20 text-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-acm-pink focus:border-transparent cursor-pointer"
```

**Checkbox:**
```tsx
className="w-4 h-4 rounded border-white/20 bg-white/10 text-acm-pink focus:ring-2 focus:ring-acm-pink cursor-pointer"
```

**Card Hover Effects:**
```tsx
// Movie cards, payment cards, etc.
className="group cursor-pointer transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-xl hover:scale-105"
```

**Disabled States:**
- Always include: `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`
- For buttons with gradient: `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`

### Modal/Popup Standards

**Overlay:**
```tsx
<div className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/70 backdrop-blur-sm" onClick={onClose} />
```

**Modal Container:**
```tsx
<div className="fixed inset-0 flex items-center justify-center z-50">
  <div className="relative w-[90vw] max-w-6xl backdrop-blur-xl rounded-3xl shadow-2xl border border-white/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-black/90 to-gray-900/90 p-6">
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Close Button (Top Right):**
```tsx
<button
  type="button"
  onClick={onClose}
  className="absolute top-5 right-6 z-[60] bg-black/50 hover:bg-black/70 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-full p-2 text-white hover:text-acm-pink duration-200 text-2xl cursor-pointer border border-white/20 hover:border-acm-pink/50"
  title="Close"
>
  <IoClose />
</button>
```

### Error Handling & User Feedback

**CRITICAL: Use Toast notifications for success/error, NOT `alert()`**

**Toast Usage (REQUIRED):**
```tsx
import { useToast } from '@/contexts/ToastContext';

const { showToast } = useToast();

// Success
showToast('Profile updated successfully', 'success');

// Error
showToast('Failed to update profile. Please try again.', 'error');

// Info
showToast('Changes will take effect immediately', 'info');
```

**Inline Error Display (Forms):**
```tsx
{error && (
  <div className="mb-4 p-3 bg-red-900/40 border border-red-500/60 rounded-md">
    <p className="text-red-200 text-sm">{error}</p>
  </div>
)}
```

**Loading States:**
```tsx
// Spinner component
<Spinner size="sm" color="pink" text="Loading..." />

// Button loading state
<button disabled={isLoading}>
  {isLoading ? 'Saving...' : 'Save Changes'}
</button>

// Full page loading
<div className="min-h-screen bg-black flex items-center justify-center">
  <div className="text-white text-xl">Loading...</div>
</div>
```

**Error States:**
```tsx
// With retry option
{error && (
  <div className="text-center py-8">
    <p className="text-red-400 mb-4">{error}</p>
    <button onClick={retry} className="text-acm-pink hover:text-acm-pink/80 cursor-pointer">
      Try Again
    </button>
  </div>
)}
```

**Empty States:**
```tsx
<div className="text-center py-8">
  <p className="text-white/60 mb-4">No items found</p>
  <button onClick={onAdd} className="text-acm-pink hover:text-acm-pink/80 cursor-pointer">
    Add Your First Item
  </button>
</div>
```

### Animation & Transitions

**Standard Transition:**
```tsx
className="transition-all duration-200"
```

**Hover Scale:**
```tsx
className="transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105"
```

**Color Transitions:**
```tsx
className="transition-colors duration-200"
```

**Smooth Slide-in (Toast, Dropdowns):**
```tsx
className="transform transition-all duration-300 translate-x-0 opacity-100"
// Hidden: "translate-x-full opacity-0"
```

### Typography

**Fonts:**
- Primary: `font-afacad` (most UI text)
- Headers: `font-red-rose` (page titles, major sections)

**Text Sizes:**
- Page titles: `text-3xl` or `text-2xl`
- Section headers: `text-xl` or `text-lg`
- Body text: `text-base` or `text-sm`
- Labels: `text-sm`
- Helper text: `text-xs`

**Font Weights:**
- Titles: `font-bold`
- Buttons: `font-semibold` or `font-bold`
- Body: `font-normal` (default)

### Layout Patterns

**Page Structure:**
```tsx
<div className="min-h-screen bg-[#1C1C1C]">
  <NavBar />
  <div className="h-30" /> {/* Spacer for fixed navbar */}
  
  <UserNavTabs activeTab="current" />
  
  <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 pb-16 mt-8">
    {/* Page content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Grid Layouts:**
```tsx
// Sidebar + Main content
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[280px_1fr] gap-12 items-start">
  <aside>{/* Sidebar */}</aside>
  <section>{/* Main content */}</section>
</div>

// Card grid
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
  {items.map(item => <Card key={item.id} {...item} />)}
</div>
```

**Spacing:**
- Page padding: `px-8 pb-16` or `px-6`
- Section margins: `mt-8`, `mb-8`
- Element gaps: `gap-4`, `gap-6`, `gap-12`
- Internal padding: `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8`

### Accessibility

**Required Attributes:**
1. **All buttons MUST have `type` attribute:**
   ```tsx
   <button type="button" onClick={...}>...</button>
   <button type="submit">...</button>
   ```

2. **All interactive elements MUST have `title` attribute:**
   ```tsx
   <button type="button" title="Close modal">...</button>
   <input type="text" title="Enter email address" />
   ```

3. **All form inputs MUST have labels:**
   ```tsx
   <label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
   <input id="email" type="email" />
   ```

4. **Images MUST have alt text:**
   ```tsx
   <Image src={...} alt="Movie poster" />
   ```

### Consistency Checklist

Before committing any UI component, verify:
- [ ] All interactive elements have `cursor-pointer`
- [ ] All buttons have `type` attribute
- [ ] All interactive elements have `title` attribute
- [ ] Uses `showToast()` instead of `alert()` for notifications
- [ ] Follows brand color system (acm-pink, acm-orange)
- [ ] Has proper hover states with transitions
- [ ] Has disabled states where applicable
- [ ] Has loading states for async operations
- [ ] Has error states with user-friendly messages
- [ ] Uses consistent spacing (px-4, py-3, gap-4, etc.)
- [ ] Uses backdrop-blur for glassmorphism effect
- [ ] Border opacity follows standards (white/10, white/20)
- [ ] Text colors follow hierarchy (white, white/80, white/60)

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Using `alert()` instead of Toast notifications**
   - BAD: `alert('Profile updated')`
   - GOOD: `showToast('Profile updated successfully', 'success')`

2. **Missing cursor pointer on interactive elements**
   - BAD: `<button onClick={...}>Click</button>`
   - GOOD: `<button onClick={...} className="cursor-pointer">Click</button>`

3. **Inconsistent button styling**
   - BAD: Custom inline styles on each button
   - GOOD: Use standard button classes from this guide

4. **Missing disabled states**
   - BAD: `<button onClick={submit}>Submit</button>`
   - GOOD: `<button onClick={submit} disabled={isLoading} className="disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed">Submit</button>`

5. **No loading feedback**
   - BAD: Button does nothing when clicked
   - GOOD: Show loading state: `{isLoading ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}`

6. **Generic error messages**
   - BAD: `Error occurred`
   - GOOD: `Failed to update profile. Please check your connection and try again.`

