## Complete Code Review Checklist

Use this checklist for every code change:

### Architecture & Design
- [ ] Follows SOLID principles
- [ ] Uses appropriate design patterns
- [ ] Fits existing architecture (Page → Hook → Client → Backend)
- [ ] No duplicate code (DRY principle)
- [ ] Single Source of Truth maintained

### Dependencies & Safety
- [ ] **Dependency analysis completed** (traced all usages with `grep`)
- [ ] **Type signature changes verified** (backward compatibility checked)
- [ ] **SSR/hydration edge cases considered**
- [ ] **Null handling verified** (no `0` sentinels, proper `null` checks)
- [ ] No breaking changes to existing functionality

### Backend (Java/Spring Boot)
- [ ] Controllers are thin (<5 lines per method)
- [ ] Business logic in service layer
- [ ] DTOs used for API boundaries (never expose entities)
- [ ] Proper use of Lombok annotations
- [ ] Import statements used (no fully qualified names)
- [ ] Static Factory Methods in dedicated Mapper classes (`mapper/` package)
- [ ] Environment variables configured correctly

### Frontend (React/Next.js)
- [ ] Components <300 lines (split if larger)
- [ ] Components <7 `useState` hooks (extract to hook if more)
- [ ] API calls in hooks, not components
- [ ] Formatting functions in `utils/`, not components
- [ ] Business logic in hooks, not components
- [ ] **Auth utilities centralized** (using `getAuthToken()`, `getUserIdFromToken()`)
- [ ] No duplicate token retrieval or JWT decoding
- [ ] SSR-safe (handles `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` unavailability)

### Code Quality
- [ ] **Comments are brief, explain WHY not WHAT**
- [ ] **NO EMOJIS in code or comments**
- [ ] **No verbose/obvious comments**
- [ ] Meaningful variable names
- [ ] Error handling implemented
- [ ] Loading states for async operations
- [ ] Type safety (no `any` without justification)

### UI/UX (Frontend)
- [ ] All interactive elements have `cursor-pointer`
- [ ] All buttons have `type` attribute
- [ ] All interactive elements have `title` attribute
- [ ] Uses `showToast()` instead of `alert()` for notifications
- [ ] Follows brand color system (acm-pink, acm-orange)
- [ ] Proper hover states with transitions
- [ ] Disabled states where applicable
- [ ] Consistent spacing and styling
- [ ] Accessibility attributes (labels, alt text)

### File Management
- [ ] Legacy/unused code identified and removed or documented
- [ ] File usage verified before deletion/modification
- [ ] No unnecessary markdown files created
- [ ] Existing docs updated instead of creating new ones

### Testing & Verification
- [ ] Happy path works
- [ ] Null/undefined handling works
- [ ] SSR doesn't crash
- [ ] Error states handled gracefully
- [ ] Type safety verified

